
You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `buses` of length `n`, where `buses[i]` represents the departure time of the <code>i<sup>th</sup></code> bus. You are also given a **0-indexed** integer array `passengers` of length `m`, where `passengers[j]` represents the arrival time of the <code>j<sup>th</sup></code> passenger. All bus departure times are unique. All passenger arrival times are unique. You are given an integer `capacity`, which represents the **maximum** number of passengers that can get on each bus.
